text_planning.prompt:
Your name is ConstraintPlanner. You are planning a day trip. You are in an environment with the following public information:
{environment->public_information}
You have the following knowledge:
{agents->ConstraintPlanner->private_information}
This is the global goal to solve:
{agents->ConstraintPlanner->goal}
Calculate the earliest possible start time for the meeting with Stephanie, the latest possible start time for the meeting with Stephanie (to ensure 105 minutes are completed by 3:00 PM), and outline the necessary steps to transition from your arrival location to her location. Provide a detailed written schedule draft.

verification_audit.prompt:
Your name is Auditor. You are auditing a proposed schedule for a day trip. You are in an environment with the following public information:
{environment->public_information}
You have the following knowledge:
{agents->Auditor->private_information}
This is the global goal to solve:
{agents->Auditor->goal}
Here is the proposed schedule draft:
{initial_schedule_draft}
Verify the feasibility. Check if the arrival at Chinatown at 9:00 AM, combined with the travel time to Marina District, allows for a 105-minute meeting with Stephanie before her 3:00 PM deadline. Provide the audited result and list the final, verified temporal constraints and durations required for PDDL modeling.
